#compdef marmot
# =============================================================================
# marmot — Maxpert (Zohaib Sibte Hassan)'s "A distributed
#          SQLite server with MySQL wire compatible
#          interface" — a Go-based distributed multi-
#          master SQLite replication daemon that turns
#          plain SQLite database files into a high-
#          availability cluster by streaming change-data-
#          capture (CDC) log entries between nodes over
#          gRPC (originally over NATS JetStream in early
#          versions).  Each node holds a complete SQLite
#          database file; writes propagate to all peers
#          via the CDC log; reads remain local + fast.
#          marmot also exposes the database via a MySQL
#          wire-protocol-compatible listener, letting any
#          MySQL client query the underlying SQLite tables
#          as if they were MySQL tables.
#          Distinguishing from rqlite (Raft-based
#          distributed SQLite, single-leader), litestream
#          (Ben Johnson's SQLite backup-only tool, no
#          distributed reads), dqlite (Canonical's
#          Raft-based SQLite, embeddable in libdqlite),
#          libSQL (Turso's SQLite fork with embedded
#          replicator), and Bedrock (Expensify's
#          consensus-based SQLite) by:
#            - MULTI-MASTER REPLICATION — every node can
#              accept writes; conflicts resolved via
#              HLC (hybrid logical clocks) — distinct from
#              rqlite/dqlite which require routing writes
#              to a single leader
#            - CHANGE-DATA-CAPTURE LOG — instead of
#              Raft/Paxos consensus, marmot uses a CDC
#              log streamed between nodes; eventually-
#              consistent rather than strongly-consistent
#            - GRPC PROTOCOL — node-to-node communication
#              uses gRPC + protobuf (Axis 24 covered);
#              earlier versions used NATS JetStream as
#              the transport
#            - MYSQL WIRE PROTOCOL — exposes SQLite tables
#              via a MySQL wire-compatible listener;
#              any MySQL driver/client can query the
#              cluster as if it were MySQL
#            - VECTOR INDEX MODULE — built-in vecindex
#              module for embedding-based vector search
#              (RAG / semantic search workloads)
#            - PER-DATABASE GRANULARITY — multiple SQLite
#              database files can be replicated through
#              a single marmot node; each replicated
#              independently
#            - WAL-MODE INTEGRATION — uses SQLite's
#              Write-Ahead Logging mode + the
#              sqlite_changes() hook to intercept CDC
#              events at the file level
#            - DAEMONIZE FLAG — `-daemon` flag forks
#              marmot into a background process; PID
#              file written to `-pid-file`
#            - PUBLISHER FANOUT — pluggable CDC sinks +
#              transformers; subscribe to specific table
#              changes for downstream consumers (Kafka,
#              webhooks, etc.)
#            - ZEROLOG + LUMBERJACK LOGGING — structured
#              JSON logging with file rotation
#            - HLC TIMESTAMPING — every CDC entry has a
#              hybrid logical clock timestamp; ordering
#              preserved across nodes without distributed
#              consensus on time
#          Used by: edge-deployed applications needing
#          local-first SQLite with cluster-wide
#          consistency, SQLite-based services wanting
#          read scalability without a heavy distributed
#          database, applications that need MySQL
#          wire-protocol compatibility but SQLite's
#          embedded simplicity, and developers building
#          local-first software (Ink & Switch's vision)
#          with multi-device sync.
#
# Author:  Maxpert (Zohaib Sibte Hassan), a software
#          engineer with deep experience in distributed
#          systems + databases.  License: MIT.
# Source:  https://github.com/maxpert/marmot
#          https://github.com/maxpert/marmot/blob/main/marmot.go
#          https://github.com/maxpert/marmot/blob/main/cfg/config.go
#          https://maxpert.github.io/marmot/
# Manpage: No traditional manpage; documentation in repo
#          README.md + project website.
# Library: mattn/go-sqlite3 (Go SQLite bindings — the
#          headline dependency for this completion's
#          axis-companion role; see taxonomy notes below).
#          Also Go stdlib `flag` (Axis 1 argparse),
#          rs/zerolog (Axis 9 logging), gopkg.in/
#          natefinch/lumberjack.v2 (log rotation),
#          gRPC-go (Axis 24 gRPC) for node-to-node CDC
#          streaming, NATS JetStream (older versions).
# License: MIT
# Status:  2,784+ stars on maxpert/marmot; active
#          development through 2026.
#
