# CROSS-LANGUAGE CLI LIBRARY TAXONOMY — AXIS 27 CONTINUES: EMBEDDED DATABASE / SQLITE BINDINGS
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# This completion **CONTINUES AXIS 27** in the cross-language CLI
# library taxonomy: Embedded Database / SQLite Bindings.
#
# Pattern: R697 Rust=82 (shellcaster/rusqlite → Axis 27 OPENS) → R698
# Go=82 (marmot/mattn-go-sqlite3 THIS) → pending R699 TS-Node=82
# (better-sqlite3 user) → R700 107th language.
#
# WHY mattn/go-sqlite3 IS A DISTINCTIVE AXIS-27 GO CHOICE:
#
#   mattn/go-sqlite3 is the original + most widely-deployed Go binding
#   to SQLite, written by Yasuhiro Matsumoto ("mattn") — the Japanese
#   developer also famous for the vim-mode-aware editor `efm-langserver`
#   and dozens of other Go libraries.  Distinguishing characteristics:
#     1. CGO-BASED — bridges to the SQLite C library via cgo;
#        upstream SQLite amalgamation is embedded in the package
#        source (no external libsqlite3-dev needed)
#     2. database/sql DRIVER — implements Go's stdlib database/sql
#        interface; users interact via the standard sql.Open("sqlite3", path)
#        pattern; ergonomic for Go developers familiar with stdlib
#        database APIs
#     3. CGO-COST TRADEOFF — cgo invocations have overhead vs pure
#        Go; this drives some users to alternatives like ncruces/
#        go-sqlite3 (WASM-based) or modernc.org/sqlite (pure Go via
#        c2go transpilation)
#     4. EXTENSION LOADING — sqlite3.SQLiteConn.LoadExtension lets
#        Go code load SQLite extensions at runtime (FTS5, json1,
#        sqlite-vec, etc.)
#     5. CUSTOM FUNCTION REGISTRATION — SQLiteConn.RegisterFunc
#        exposes Go functions as user-defined SQL functions
#     6. WAL + JOURNAL MODES — full control over journal_mode,
#        synchronous, mmap_size, page_size pragmas
#     7. BUSY TIMEOUT — `_busy_timeout=ms` DSN parameter
#     8. CRYPTO + SEE EDITIONS — supports SQLite Encryption Extension
#        (SEE) via build tags; useful for at-rest encryption
#     9. PRE-DATES MOST ALTERNATIVES — first released 2014; the
#        original Go SQLite binding; most Go SQLite tooling
#        defaults to mattn/go-sqlite3 unless they have specific
#        reasons to avoid cgo
#    10. ~9,000+ stars on mattn/go-sqlite3
#
# Maintained by Yasuhiro Matsumoto (mattn).  License: MIT.
#
